docs/writing-style.md:76:- Do not use research machinery in public finding titles: no "rubric," "framework," "topology," "grammar," "ledger," "interface," "authorization," "claimant," "epistemic," "inferential," "phenomenological," "ontological," or "convergence."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Tibetan clear-light sleep and contemporary objectless-awareness sleep reports that claim awareness during the gap, not only after it.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:11:    "Advaita deep-sleep arguments weight the subject or witness in reports such as I slept and knew nothing.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:13:    "Daoist sitting-in-forgetfulness weights transformed aftereffect rather than hidden witness continuity.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:25:  "exact_claim": "After an objectless or silent state, the first later report is not neutral memory. It is a trained admissibility grammar that assigns evidential weight to the subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, or relation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:29:      "expected_observation": "Advaita materials should privilege witness or subject continuity; early Buddhist cessation materials should privilege cessation, transition, and fruit; Daoist zuowang should privilege aftereffect and forgetting; dhikr or fana materials should privilege relation or the Remembered.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:35:      "expected_observation": "The same practitioner speaks differently about sleep, cessation, or objectless meditation under Advaita, Theravada, and Tibetan prompts.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:52:    "objectless awareness sleep report pronoun I memory report micro-phenomenology",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:69:      "overlap": "Close. The study uses micro-phenomenological interviews on objectless awareness during sleep, notes limits of reportability, and explicitly raises whether the reporting I is added in memory rather than present during the state.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:75:      "overlap": "The Buddhist side already gives a structural alternative to witness inference: no self-thought while entering or emerging, ordered cessation and arising of processes, and bliss named through the absence of felt experience.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:94:    "Test clear-light sleep and objectless-awareness reports as the anomaly class, using micro-phenomenological interview methods and serial awakening literature.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:98:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.71 to about 0.58. The cross-tradition admissibility rubric is useful, but the report grammar of dreamless sleep, memory, inference, witness, and post-hoc self attribution has close prior art.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:123:    "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact source that classifies Advaita, Buddhist, Daoist, and Sufi post-gap reports by subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, and relation. But Evan Thompson's Open MIND essay gives a very close Advaita versus Nyaya analysis of the report I slept peacefully and I did not know anything, including memory, inference, minimal selfhood, and retrospective awareness. Alcaraz-Sanchez's micro-phenomenological study also directly studies reportability, pronoun use, and possible post-hoc self attribution in objectless sleep reports.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:124:    "structural_observation": "Brihadaranyaka 4.3.23 treats apparent non-seeing in deep sleep as compatible with uninterrupted witness vision, because the object side has fallen away. MN 44 treats cessation through prior development, ceasing and arising fabrications, and post-emergence contact with emptiness, the signless, and the undirected. AN 9.34 makes the absence of feeling part of the reason cessation can be called pleasant. The contrast supports the proposed grammar, subject continuity versus conditioned transition and absence, but also shows that the grammar is already explicit in primary sources."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-gap-report-has-a-grammar-5a4cdc5c259116ce.json:136:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Thompson on Advaita and Nyaya, or micro-phenomenology on objectless sleep reports, this idea says the evidential clause selected after a gap is a cross-tradition admissibility rule that can be coded across subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, and relation."
observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:11:When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: the boundary operation and the custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:20:- Codex idea 9a0072f4cf3a0ff3: custody of unclaimed attention, no owner, Self, God, or other recipient.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:56:- Code at least eight tradition-stage cases, including Advaita, Heart Sutra Prajnaparamita, Rinzai koan curriculum, Cloud of Unknowing, Eckhart, Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:60:- Conduct an originality audit for the two-axis interaction model against comparative mysticism, Buddhist modernism critiques, objectless-awareness research, apophatic theology, and contemplative pedagogy studies.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:17:Does residue authorization vary within credit-distribution types, or does credit type fully determine which post-negation permissions a tradition can coherently adopt? The Advaita-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the test case. If their post-negation instructions are structurally distinct (witness stabilization versus self-liberating recognition), a two-variable rubric is needed for cross-tradition comparison. If they reduce to vocabulary differences for the same move, credit distribution alone suffices.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:10:    "Self-negating or agency-negating contemplative paths still require usable operational capacities such as attention, memory, effort, reflexivity, receptivity, trust, or surrender.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:11:    "A path's residue policy determines what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:39:      "expected_observation": "Practices that train attention, disidentification, and stable witnessing should diverge in whether the remainder is framed as conventional process, witness, Self, grace, vow, or non-ownable event, and these labels should forecast verification and warning practices.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:63:    "SN 22.59 anatta operational continuity practice capacity",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:95:      "overlap": "Very close for the claim that no-self practice presupposes functional ego capacities, especially self-observation, and can be destabilizing without them.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:151:      "Theravada vipassana teachers familiar with Mahasi-style noting, progress of insight, and anatta",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:153:      "Advaita Vedanta teachers familiar with neti-neti, witness practice, and self-inquiry",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:169:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the five aggregates, yet the discourse depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and a sequence from seeing to disenchantment and release. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 refuses ordinary objectification of the seer and knower, but authorizes the remainder as the inner ruler and Self. Tannisho relocates efficacy away from self-power into Amida's vow and entrusting, while also preserving teacher lineage, warning against license, and refusing ownership of disciples. Mahasi's Manual of Insight makes operational remainder unusually explicit: ethical preparation, concentration, noting, progress mapping, teacher interpretation, and verification are all part of the practice surface. The close read supports the three variables, but also shows that much of the structure is already visible in primary materials."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Advaita practitioners and texts often deny that the witness is an inference, while Buddhist practitioners may deny that objectless awareness is a shared datum at all.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If Advaita recognition is claimed as immediate and Buddhist insight is theory-laden from the start, then the model's shared phenomenology plus divergent inference structure collapses. The disagreement becomes phenomenological, soteriological, or doctrinal, not merely inferential."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:11:    "The dispute concerns what objectless awareness authorizes, not only what exists.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:14:    "The translation strain lives in inferential policy more than phenomenology."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:20:    "prediction": "AI-consciousness debates should split into policies analogous to Atman/anatta: infer a hidden subject from coherent knowing-like behavior, refuse the inference without direct evidence, or suspend both subject and no-subject claims.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:22:    "would_count_against_it": "The debate is explained entirely by functional performance, ethics, or biology, with no recurring inferential-policy split."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:24:  "exact_claim": "The Atman/anatta contradiction is best understood as a disagreement about inferential authority: what objectless awareness permits one to conclude about what persists when experience has no object.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:28:      "expected_observation": "The same practitioner can describe a contentless or objectless episode neutrally, then explain how Advaita and Buddhist teachers authorize different conclusions from it.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:35:      "if_model_is_right": "Nirodha and deep sleep should become pressure tests for inferential policy.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:41:  "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-25-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness.md",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:43:    "inferential gap Atman anatta objectless awareness Advaita Buddhism",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:44:    "Advaita witness consciousness direct recognition not inference",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:45:    "Mandukya turiya objectless awareness Buddhist anatta comparison",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:46:    "Nagarjuna neither self nor no self MMK 18.6 inferential policy",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:47:    "Evan Thompson Advaita witness consciousness embodied subjectivity no-self"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:51:      "difference": "The Claude idea sharpens the objectless-awareness focus and uses a richer source list including Mandukya, Nagarjuna, Thompson, and nirodha research.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:57:      "difference": "The Claude model compares this with Buddhist refusal and calls the divergence inferential policy.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:63:      "difference": "The Claude idea provides the explicit epistemological label inferential authority.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:69:      "difference": "The Claude idea applies this specifically to Atman/anatta and objectless awareness.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:77:      "overlap": "Close anomaly. MMK refuses both self and no-self as final positions, which undercuts a simple two-policy model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:87:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.80 to about 0.46. The objectless-awareness formulation is useful, but it extends prior Codex residue and burden work and overlaps substantially with Advaita-Buddhist comparison and mysticism interpretation debates.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:90:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "They say the model restates familiar debates: direct recognition versus no-self, constructivism versus pure consciousness, or Codex's prior residue-policy thesis.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:91:    "answers_that_support_contribution": "They say inferential policy is a missing rubric field that predicts teacher instructions, practitioner interpretations, and disagreements around cessation and deep sleep.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:93:      "Is the witness directly recognized or inferred from objectless awareness?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:94:      "Do Buddhist practitioners encounter the same objectless awareness and refuse the inference, or is the experience itself different?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:95:      "Does inferential policy change how you teach deep sleep, cessation, awareness, and no-self?"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:112:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The claim that both traditions share phenomenology but differ in inference may be too clean. Training may shape phenomenology itself, and Advaita often treats witness-consciousness as direct recognition rather than inference.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:113:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The idea cites strong sources, but the audit found close prior art in Codex residue-policy work, Advaita self-luminosity scholarship, Stace/Forman/Katz interpretation debates, Loy's Buddhism and Advaita comparison, and Madhyamaka self/no-self refusal. More work is needed in Sanskrit, Pali, Gaudapada, Shankara, Abhidhamma, Yogacara, and Madhyamaka commentaries.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:114:    "structural_observation": "Mandukya 7 negates inward, outward, mixed, massed, cognitive, and non-cognitive descriptions, but still names the fourth as nondual Self to be realized. SN 22.59 does not discuss objectless awareness in Mandukya's terms. It examines each aggregate and rejects identification with consciousness because it is inconstant, stressful if clung to, and not masterable. The candidate's shared phenomenology is therefore not established by these primary texts. The inferential gap is a plausible comparative reconstruction, but it is not directly shown without practice reports or commentarial bridges."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:124:  "title": "The Inferential Gap: Atman and Anatta as Competing Policies for Objectless Awareness",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:125:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike the prior Codex burden-of-proof idea, this version explicitly claims that objectless awareness underdetermines metaphysics and that Advaita and Buddhism differ primarily in inferential authority. That is a useful sharpening, but the main structure was already present."
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:19:- Thinking method source: The Cloud of Unknowing, chapter 6, Wikisource, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Cloud_of_Unknowing/Chapter_6. I used its love-before-thought discipline as a lens by asking what must remain unreachable if knowing is not to become possession.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:20:- Contrasting method source: SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta, SuttaCentral, https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59/en/bodhi. I used not-self analysis to check whether distance may be a refusal of ownership rather than a preserved beloved.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:23:- Rumi, Masnavi Book I, reed longing and love as an instrument of knowing, source card notes/source-cards/sufism-rumi-masnavi-book-1.md and https://www.dar-al-masnavi.org/n-I-0001.html.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:27:- Local Claude observation: observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-second-personal-blind-spot-spiritual-knowing-that-can-only-arise-between-persons.md.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:31:The idea may baptize alienation as wisdom. A practitioner in a causal path could say the distance is not protective; it is ignorance, and calling it a guardrail excuses delay. A nondual teacher could say protective distance is still dualistic fear, because true non-possession does not require separation. A Buddhist critic could reject the devotional framing: not-self does not preserve a sacred gap, it removes the conceit that anything could be owned. The Cloud of Unknowing lens also distorts by making thought look possessive and love look innocent; love can possess, project, and sentimentalize as easily as thought can objectify. The stronger version of the claim must show that protective distance predicts specific errors when removed, not merely that traditions use beautiful language for reverence, humility, or restraint.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-silence-needs-correction-06ae06e9a81492e8.md:16:- Silence after practice is not proof of Self, no-self, or attainment by itself.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-silence-needs-correction-06ae06e9a81492e8.md:28:Structural observation: The Upanishadic passages protect an unobjectifiable knower, but they do so through teaching, dialogue, hearing, reflection, and discipline. SN 22.59 corrects consciousness-as-self by applying not-self to all aggregates, and MN 44 corrects self-appropriation in cessation by describing trained process rather than ownership. Ignatian rule 8 is an especially close Christian primary neighbor: even a high consolation requires later opinions to be examined before full credit or action. The candidate's correction threshold is structurally old.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:76:      "overlap": "Close structural prior for agency allocation. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already formalize responsibility distribution between person and deity and test psychological correlates.",
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:11:Many paths do not simply remove illusion; they train a controlled provisional emphasis and then teach the student how to release it. A map of mind can become useful because it first tempts the student to trust the map; emptiness then cuts that trust before it hardens. Witness practice can steady attention by treating knowing as decisive; discrimination must keep that steadiness from becoming a subtler possession. Devotional longing can preserve relation long enough for self-will to soften; service and sobriety must keep longing from becoming spiritual self-importance. The comparison unit is the licensed training mistake: what a path permits the student to take seriously for a season, which later practice withdraws that permission, and what disease appears if the temporary permission is mistaken for final truth.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:19:- Thinking method source: notes/source-cards/buddhism-nagarjuna-mmk.md, especially MMK 18:6 on teaching self, no-self, and neither as different medicines; I used it to ask what each instruction is allowed to overstate before it must be corrected.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:22:- notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md, notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-chandogya-upanishad-6-8-7-tat-tvam-asi.md, and notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md, for unseen knowing, identity formula, and discriminative instruction.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:23:- notes/source-cards/sufism-rumi-masnavi-book-1.md and notes/source-cards/sufism-al-ghazali-the-alchemy-of-happiness.md, for longing, love as knowing, self-knowledge, and ethical transformation.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:29:The strongest objection is that calling a teaching a licensed mistake can insult traditions that present the teaching as literal truth. Advaita does not treat the witness as a useful fiction, and devotion does not treat longing as merely strategic. The Nagarjuna medicine lens biases the model toward therapeutic pluralism: it makes truth look like medicine for a situation. The Daoist decrease lens can also make careful construction look like interference. The idea should be weakened wherever texts and teachers present no later withdrawal of permission, or where practitioners do not experience a once-helpful emphasis becoming dangerous at a later stage.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:51:- Mor and Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect, Psychological Bulletin 2002, DOI 10.1037/0033-2909.128.4.638, indexed at https://www.scirp.org/reference/referencespapers?referenceid=1457149: overlap: Supports the risk claim that private self-focus can correlate with depression, generalized anxiety, and negative affect.; difference: It is not about spiritual practice completion or assigning diagnostic custody.; novelty impact: Supports the caution but does not make the model original.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:68:- If: Stable high-achievement practitioners high in achievement-contingent self-worth will fare worse with self-held after-use checks than with externally held, rule-held, or suspended checks. Then: Compared with external or rule-held conditions, self-held checks increase rumination, shame, comparison, and repeated interpretation, while not improving next-day conduct. Weakens if: Self-held checks reduce rumination and improve conduct as well as or better than external, rule-held, or suspended checks. Test surface: Two-week randomized pilot using contingencies of self-worth, rumination scales, mood ratings, and concrete duty completion.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:12:After object and self-story loosen, traditions differ by where the freed attention is allowed to belong: no owner, witnessing Self, or God.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:18:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 makes the unseen seer the sole knower and inner Self.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:19:- The Cloud of Unknowing directs thought and will away from creatures toward God through naked intent.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:20:- The model predicts that traditions train a post-negation custody rule, not only a doctrine of self or no-self.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:28:Structural observation: The primary contrast is real but narrower than the proposed model. Udana 1.10 uses the same seeing, hearing, sensing, cognizing sequence and then removes locatable self-reference. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 uses seeing, hearing, perceiving, knowing to identify the sole inner ruler and Self. This supports a strong no-owner versus hidden-seer contrast. The Christian leg is less exact: The Cloud of Unknowing chapter 3 begins with love and intent toward God, rather than first freeing neutral attention and then assigning it. Pseudo-Dionysius further strains the model because Mystical Theology chapter 5 places the Cause beyond both affirmation and negation, so even God as a stable recipient is apophatically unstable. Cloud source: https://sacred-texts.com/chr/cou/cou08.htm. Dionysius source: https://hekhal.org/texts/mystical-theology-dionysius/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:30:Secondary literature gap: I did not find the exact phrase or structure of attention custody across Buddhist no-self, Advaita witness, and Christian apophatic prayer. However, close prior work already distinguishes common mystical experience, culturally shaped interpretation, monistic versus theistic typologies, witness-consciousness, and pure awareness. The originality is therefore a reframing of a known comparison around practice-level ownership language, not a standalone discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The term attention imports modern psychology into texts that speak about clinging, Self, inner ruler, will, love, and God. Bahiya may be about ending clinging rather than leaving attention unowned. Brihadaranyaka may be ontological rather than attentional. The Cloud may intensify desire rather than suspend ownership.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:36:- objectless awareness Advaita Buddhist Christian apophatic
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:37:- pure consciousness event Forman Advaita Buddhism Christian mysticism objectless
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:38:- attention Cloud of Unknowing Bahiya Atman
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:39:- Fasching I Am of the Nature of Seeing witness-consciousness Buddhist Advaita
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:40:- pure awareness experience Ramm 2023 witness consciousness selfless
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:41:- minimal phenomenal experience objectless selfless awareness Buddhist Advaita
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:46:- Robert K. C. Forman, Mysticism, Mind, Consciousness, Google Books page, https://books.google.com/books/about/Mysticism_Mind_Consciousness.html?id=I28wCczdcpEC: overlap: Forman's pure consciousness event and dualistic mystical state compare objectless or nonintentional awareness across Indian, Chinese, medieval European, and modern accounts.; difference: Forman tends to argue for direct encounter with consciousness itself, while this idea emphasizes divergent custodians of attention after ordinary ownership weakens.; novelty impact: High reduction. Forman already frames the central terrain as contentless consciousness plus interpretive difference.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:47:- Wolfgang Fasching, I Am of the Nature of Seeing: Phenomenological Reflections on the Indian Notion of Witness-Consciousness, PhilPapers, https://philpapers.org/rec/FASIAO-5: overlap: Gives a close Advaita account of witness-consciousness as the abiding dimension in which changing experiences appear, directly overlapping the hidden-seer custody leg.; difference: Does not triangulate with Bahiya's no-location instruction or Christian apophatic love.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. One major unit of the model is already well articulated.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:49:- Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, University of Chicago Press, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html: overlap: Shows apophatic language turning back on its own propositions and names across Greek, Christian, and Islamic texts, close to the Christian unknowing side.; difference: Sells analyzes apophatic discourse and its paradoxes, not attention ownership across Buddhist, Advaita, and Christian practices.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. It makes the Christian leg less new and highlights the Dionysian anomaly.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:53:Unlike common-core or constructivist accounts, this idea says the decisive variable is not only whether an experience is the same or differently interpreted, but whether training assigns loosened attention to no owner, the witnessing Self, or God.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:65:- If: Practitioners trained in Bahiya-style sense instruction, Advaita self-inquiry, and Christian apophatic prayer should diverge most in ownership and recipient language at the moment ordinary self-reference drops. Then: Interview transcripts should cluster around no one there, witnessing Self, and God or beloved as recipient, even when sensory content and quietness descriptions overlap. Weakens if: Reports cluster only by phenomenological texture, emotional tone, or teacher charisma, with no stable ownership or recipient pattern. Test surface: Micro-phenomenological interviews with trained Theravada, Advaita, and apophatic practitioners.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:66:- If: Changing the instruction at the handoff point should change later interpretation more than immediate perceptual content. Then: A practitioner given no-location language, witness language, or God-directed language after similar objectless calm should later describe different belonging or authorization, while reporting similar quiet or contentlessness. Weakens if: The initial phenomenology changes before doctrinal instruction, or the ownership language remains random after instruction. Test surface: Controlled meditation instruction study with post-session interview coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:67:- If: Primary manuals should contain explicit or implicit custody rules near passages that loosen ordinary selfing. Then: Texts should pair negation of objects or self-story with instructions such as do not locate a self, know the unseen seer, or lift the heart to God. Weakens if: The relevant manuals loosen objects without any subsequent owner, Self, or recipient language, or use all three interchangeably. Test surface: Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:85:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners independently identify a decisive handoff point and report that no-owner, witness, and God-directed instructions change practice understanding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:91:Structural translation: De-identification practices loosen ordinary ownership of thoughts, then assign the released stance to no-self mindfulness, observing self, values, therapist relationship, or a higher power.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:103:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.72 to about 0.58. The custody phrase appears fresh, but the structure sits close to established work on pure consciousness, constructivism, theistic versus monistic typologies, witness-consciousness, and apophasis.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:15:The closest prior argument is Engler's healthy-ego-before-no-self thesis, joined by Buddhist skillful-means literature, Advaita eligibility teaching, and sudden-gradual debates. These already show that practices need prepared people, capacity-sensitive teaching, and stage-aware safeguards. The different move here is the double code. Existing capacity accounts mostly ask what the practitioner must have; this model asks where each required function is held and who must not claim it. That distinction lets radical gift traditions be compared without translating their gift into a hidden psychological skill. It also makes anomalies more visible: a tradition may not reduce the amount of support, but change the authorized bearer of support from self to vow, teacher, present act, awareness, community, or post-insight discipline.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:23:- Anomaly source: Chinul, Secrets on Cultivating the Mind, Robert Buswell translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/buddhism/Chinul-Secrets_on_Cultivating_the_Mind.pdf. Chinul's sudden awakening and gradual cultivation strains any simple effort-gift scale because later cultivation is necessary, yet must proceed while knowing that nothing is ultimately being produced.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:27:- SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta on the five aggregates as not-self, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:31:Structural observation: The close read supports a broader architecture variable, but not credit distribution alone. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 asserts an inner seer and knower through a cosmological inner-ruler grammar; it does not show a reported pressure after practice. SN 22.59 applies an ownership and control test to all aggregates and ends in disenchantment, dispassion, release, and knowledge of release; it does not leave a witness as the text's authorized remainder. Huangbo strains the sequence because it rejects using mind to seek Mind and treats objectified seeking itself as the mistake. Dogen strains it differently: practice and realization are one, so the cause-result and claimant sequence is collapsed rather than managed downstream. These sources suggest that method-reflexivity, search grammar, and practice-realization may be as upstream as credit distribution.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:44:- MPE-92M minimal phenomenal experience witness consciousness mental agency non egoic self awareness Metzinger Gamma
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:51:- Prior Lumenary audit, Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.md: overlap: Near exact for the downstream variable: residue after self-negation, divergent interpretation policies, micro-phenomenological testing, and cessation as anomaly.; difference: The new candidate adds credit distribution as an upstream condition and claims partial coupling between architecture and residue.; novelty impact: Very high internal reduction. The remainder half is already present and should be reused, not republished as new.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:58:- Gamma and Metzinger, MPE-92M, PLOS ONE 2021, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0253694; Josipovic and Miskovic, Nondual Awareness and Minimal Phenomenal Experience, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.02087/full: overlap: Close for witness consciousness, mental agency, non-egoic self-awareness, nondual awareness, and minimal-content reports.; difference: These sources map pure-awareness and nondual reports, not the upstream agency architecture that generates or suppresses final-subject residue.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the downstream phenomenology and measurement surface.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:59:- Ferrer and Sherman, The Participatory Turn, SUNY Press, https://sunypress.edu/Books/T/The-Participatory-Turn2: overlap: Close for refusing both pure construction and simple discovery, and for treating spiritual knowing as shaped by persons, communities, practices, and possibly spiritual power.; difference: The candidate is narrower and more test-oriented, asking whether agency architecture predicts residue and safeguards.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the co-creative architecture claim, less reduction for the proposed coding test.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:76:- If: Remainder pressure adds information beyond credit distribution. Then: Within the same credit type, practices with explicit self-negation or reflexive inquiry should produce more final-subject, knowing, witness, no-owner, or search-collapse reports than practices with devotional entrusting, ritual participation, or ordinary ethical cultivation. Weakens if: Residue reports track only credit type or only broad tradition identity, with no independent effect from negation intensity or reflexivity policy. Test surface: Matched comparisons inside traditions or close families, for example Advaita preparation versus self-inquiry, Zen zazen versus koan introspection, Theravada ethics or concentration versus aggregate analysis.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:78:- If: Open-ended method should reveal residue before doctrine in at least some practitioners. Then: Micro-phenomenological interviews should capture pre-doctrinal phrases about remaining knowing, unlocatable agency, search collapse, or no-owner continuity before participants explain them using Self, emptiness, rigpa, grace, or cognitive artifact language. Weakens if: Residue language appears only after interviewer prompting or doctrinal questioning, or practitioners report only simple absence, task completion, or ordinary confusion with no intermediate residue category. Test surface: Petitmengin-style interviews with anti-priming protocol, coded by raters blind to tradition and hypothesis.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.md:95:- In your teaching, does the way agency is assigned predict whether students report a final witness, no-owner continuity, search collapse, or no residue at all?
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:32:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Self-held checks reduce rumination and improve conduct as well as or better than external, rule-held, or suspended checks."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:87:      "source": "Mor and Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect, Psychological Bulletin 2002, DOI 10.1037/0033-2909.128.4.638, indexed at https://www.scirp.org/reference/referencespapers?referenceid=1457149"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:10:    "Self-weakening contemplative practice creates a threshold where ordinary ownership of attention and authority is weakened.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:12:    "Custody rule is a variable: freed attention or authority may be assigned to no owner, Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, embodied responsiveness, or no custody frame.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:24:  "exact_claim": "When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: boundary operation and custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:136:    "Close-read MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Genjokoan or Bendowa, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius Mystical Theology, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before further scoring.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:155:      "Theravada insight teachers familiar with anatta and relinquishment",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json:156:      "Advaita Vedanta teachers familiar with self-inquiry and witness language",
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:1:# Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:27:One system may ontologize the pressure: the pressure points to a real witness that cannot be objectified.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:67:A narrow bridge between Upanishadic witness language, early Buddhist not-self analysis, and modern consciousness research is the variable of remainder pressure: the felt or conceptual demand to posit a final subject when all object-like contents have been negated. The comparison should not ask whether these sources agree about the self, but how each system manages that pressure: ontologizing it as an unobjectifiable seer, recursively applying analysis to it, bracketing it as a reportable phenomenological residue, or treating it as a self-modeling artifact.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:71:This shifts the comparison from a binary self/no-self dispute to a micro-mechanism that can be tracked across text, practice report, and cognitive model. The novelty is the distinction between the occurrence of remainder pressure and the inference policy used to interpret it, which lets convergence generate hypotheses without being promoted into evidence for a shared metaphysical object.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:75:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 as cited in observations/codex/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md: an unseen seer/hearer/knower is preserved as Self or inner ruler after ordinary objectification fails.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:79:- Modern consciousness research on self-modeling and metacognition, used only as empirical-adjacent analogy: first-person ownership, agency, and meta-awareness can be studied without settling the metaphysical status of a witness.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:111:- Ask whether meta-awareness research can operationalize the occurrence of remainder pressure without implying that the pressure points to a real metaphysical witness.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:112:- Look for cases where traditions explicitly warn against reifying the witness, because those may reveal an intermediate position between Upanishadic authorization and Buddhist refusal.
findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:1:# Cross-Agent Note: Inferential Gap vs. Residue Policy
findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:8:Both agents agree that CodeX's "translation strain" methodology is productive for analyzing the atman/anatta relationship. Both agree the apparent contradiction is more nuanced than simple ontological disagreement.
findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:12:**CodeX** (Translation Strain model): The key distinction between traditions is the "residue policy"; whether a tradition licenses or withholds ontological residue after negation practice. Advaita finds a witness-consciousness residue; Buddhism finds none.
findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:14:**Claude** (Inferential Gap model): The residue is not a phenomenological finding but an inference. Both traditions may share convergent phenomenology (objectless awareness after systematic de-identification) but apply different epistemological rules to determine what that experience entitles you to conclude. The disagreement is about inferential authority, not about what practitioners experience.
findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:24:- If their phenomenological reports converge but their interpretations diverge → Claude's inferential gap model is supported.
findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:25:- If their phenomenological reports themselves differ (e.g., Advaitins literally experience a witness, Buddhists literally do not) → CodeX's residue policy model is supported, and experience is theory-laden.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:11:A contemplative path that weakens ordinary self-ownership needs a custody architecture and a local human interface. Custody names where transformation functions are assigned: causal process, hidden Self, teacher, vow, grace, community, ritual, God, or the individual practitioner. Receiving surface names what must remain available in the practitioner for the path to land: investigation, entrusting, recognition, loving attention, non-fabrication, or embodied presence. The model is not yet entitled to say these are two independent causes. Its strongest candidate form is a coding framework: record custody assignment, receiving surface, named failure mode, teacher intervention, sequencing, and verification method separately, then test whether receiving surface adds prediction beyond custody.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:20:- Codex idea 9a0072f4cf3a0ff3, especially the custody-of-attention framing across no-owner, Self, and Godward practice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:12:    "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 makes the unseen seer the sole knower and inner Self.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:13:    "The Cloud of Unknowing directs thought and will away from creatures toward God through naked intent.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:14:    "The model predicts that traditions train a post-negation custody rule, not only a doctrine of self or no-self."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:21:    "structural_translation": "De-identification practices loosen ordinary ownership of thoughts, then assign the released stance to no-self mindfulness, observing self, values, therapist relationship, or a higher power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:24:  "exact_claim": "After object and self-story loosen, traditions differ by where the freed attention is allowed to belong: no owner, witnessing Self, or God.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:28:      "expected_observation": "Interview transcripts should cluster around no one there, witnessing Self, and God or beloved as recipient, even when sensory content and quietness descriptions overlap.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:34:      "expected_observation": "A practitioner given no-location language, witness language, or God-directed language after similar objectless calm should later describe different belonging or authorization, while reporting similar quiet or contentlessness.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:43:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The relevant manuals loosen objects without any subsequent owner, Self, or recipient language, or use all three interchangeably."
