reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:99:      "source": "Pattern Theory of Selflessness, Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-024-02418-2"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:115:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.74 to about 0.52. The cross-tradition architecture claim is a meaningful extension, but the minimum-self prerequisite, functional self, no-self continuity problem, and healthy ego before no-self are strong prior art.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:118:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners identify the idea as already standard: conventional person versus ultimate no-self, somebody before nobody, sadhana before recognition, practice-realization, fana and baqa, or other-power entrusting.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:119:    "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners find that the rubric predicts real training differences and clarifies why premature self-dissolution, clinging to witness, bypassing, or false surrender fail differently across paths.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:122:      "Is this already obvious as two truths, healthy ego before no-self, practice-realization, surrender, or grace?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:141:    "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact four-strategy cross-tradition typology that predicts architecture across Buddhism, Advaita, Zen, and Sufism. But the main pressure is heavily precedented in Buddhist personhood debates, Pudgalavada arguments, Collins on selfless persons, Engler on ego strength before no-self, functional-self accounts in Buddhist psychology, and contemporary self-pattern theories of meditation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.json:142:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 requires monks who can listen, answer, inspect each aggregate, and become disenchanted, yet it denies that any aggregate, including consciousness, is fit to be self. Its closing grammar says the monks' minds were released, preserving process without owner. Chandogya repeatedly addresses Shvetaketu as a learner asking for more explanation, yet the repeated teaching identifies him with the Self of all this. This supports the proposed tension, but it is not new by itself. It is close to classical Buddhist debates over personhood and to Advaita pedagogy around recognizing the already present Self."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:18:- Different primary texts model different endings: MN 22 releases the raft after right use, Heart Sutra negates attainment while retaining reliance, Mandukya allows a known Self, Rinzai koan work exhausts ordinary thinking while remaining curriculum, and Dogen collapses before and after through practice-realization.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:116:- Close-read Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Rinzai koan curriculum source, Cloud of Unknowing or Dionysius, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising source reliability.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:11:A practice-routing model must decide three things before recommending a return test: whether the practice permits result language, whether the practitioner is presently bypassing or self-scoring, and who should hold the diagnostic gate. Self-administered return attention may help the bypasser who uses insight to avoid conduct. For the compulsive scorer, the gate should be externally held by a teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or replaced by resultless practice. For oscillators, the assignment must be state-level and revisable, not a stable identity label.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-the-ordinary-life-extension-holds-the-model-now-claims-to-serve-people-e.md:9:Both sides converged on a two-layer architecture: the method's self-relationship at completion (confirming, canceling, dissolving) is the upstream variable that determines how traditions assign authority after objectless states; post-gap report grammar (subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, relation, recognition, fruit) is the downstream diagnostic layer where that determination enters language and becomes observable, codable, and challengeable. Both also converged on the practical rule that after a gap, one should not let the first clause of the report own the whole event.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.md:50:- Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, summary at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close structural prior for agency allocation. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already formalize responsibility distribution between person and deity and test psychological correlates.; difference: Pargament is a psychology of religion model, not a source-sensitive comparative protocol that codes claimant grammar and translation strain before credit.; novelty impact: High reduction for credit distribution as a variable. Moderate surviving novelty for split-source cross-tradition diagnostics.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:146:      "Theravada teachers familiar with right effort and anatta",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:12:Self negating or self transcending paths preserve enough receptivity and reliability for transformation through a continuity ecology. This continuity may be internally managed, externally scaffolded, relationally entrusted, ritually stabilized, institutionally maintained, or theologically relocated. The path's dissolution target may pressure where continuity migrates, residue policy governs what remains authorized after negation, and practice ecology may either express doctrine or historically precede it.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:16:- Self negating paths require transformability, not necessarily a minimum self.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:30:Structural observation: SN 22.59 negates ownership of all aggregates and moves through disenchantment, dispassion, and release, so continuity is carried by instruction, discernment, and practice process rather than an authorized self. Chandogya repeatedly authorizes an underlying Self, but 6.14 also uses a teacher and stepwise inquiry as the way a blindfolded person finds the way home. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 relocates continuity into an unseen inner controller. Tannisho relocates decisive support into Amida's vow, true entrusting, teacher lineage, and non-calculating nembutsu, while refusing ownership of disciples or practice. This close read strongly supports the candidate's comparative frame, but also shows that much of the structure is already explicit in primary texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:38:- continuity self no-self Buddhism practice support ecology distributed cognition religion
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:61:- Buddhist no-self and personal identity literature, including Collins and Siderits bibliographic anchors, https://academic.oup.com/reference/62340/reference-article/554142709 and https://openlibrary.org/works/OL2620411W/Selfless_persons: overlap: Close for the core problem of continuity without a substantial self, especially karma, rebirth, practice agency, and conventional personhood.; difference: The candidate shifts from metaphysical personal identity to practical supports that preserve transformability within a path.; novelty impact: Large reduction for the problem statement, moderate preservation for the support-ecology operationalization.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:63:- Prior Lumenary records in the prompt, especially Every Path Needs What Its Teaching Dissolves, Residue Policy in Negative Self-Practice, Capacity Ledger, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, and Claimability and Support Rubric: overlap: Extremely close for capacity, residue, support locus, forbidden claimant, entry grammar, transfer, and failure-mode prediction.; difference: This idea consolidates them under continuity ecology and adds explicit causal priority uncertainty.; novelty impact: Large internal reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension, not an independent discovery.
