reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.json:148:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found close prior structures in religious coping styles, self-power and other-power, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Engler on ego strength before no-self, the Buddhist raft and upaya pattern, and local Lumenary capacity-ledger and credit-distribution work. I did not find the exact field list as a cross-tradition coding sheet, but the core agency-allocation and means-end reversal are well established.",
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:11:Before a path can tell a student what is true, it has to shape the kind of receiver the student becomes. Advaita trains a receiver that trusts non-objectifiable knowing; early Buddhism trains one that refuses to own any arising thing; Daoism trains one that waits without forcing; Sufism trains one that can be addressed by the beloved; relational traditions train a receiver that exists between persons, not inside one person. The shared silence after practice is therefore not raw data waiting for doctrine. It is already filtered by the receiving posture the practice has built. Cross-tradition comparison should ask a prior question: what kind of arrival can this method recognize without betraying itself?
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:21:- notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md and notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md, for unseen knower language and non-objectifiable knowing.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:22:- notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md, for the not-self analysis of the aggregates and the refusal to appropriate experience as self.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:28:- observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-second-personal-blind-spot-spiritual-knowing-that-can-only-arise-between-persons.md, for Buber, Levinas, Ubuntu, Confucian, Jewish liturgical, and Zen transmission evidence that some knowing may be relational rather than solitary.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:57:- Build a reception-policy rubric with fields for trained receiver, trusted arrival, rejected arrival, likely blind spot, correcting practice, and unit of knowing.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-receiver-precedes-the-revelation.md:59:- Compare two methods at the same post-quiet moment: what can arrive as insight for a witness-trained receiver, a non-appropriating receiver, a non-forcing receiver, and a relational receiver?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:29:      "expected_observation": "Vipassana-trained practitioners attempting Advaita self-inquiry should initially keep tracking change and non-ownership rather than resting in witness-recognition. Advaita-trained practitioners attempting vipassana should tend to seek a stable knower or background rather than evenly noting impermanence. Practitioners trained in non-attachment who enter devotional surrender should report affective restraint or suspicion of dependence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:37:      "test_surface": "Blind coding of Visuddhimagga chapter 1, Vivekachudamani vv. 17-30, Cloud of Unknowing chapters 3-6, al-Qushayri's Risala, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, and Satipatthana-related materials.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:41:      "expected_observation": "Witness-trained practitioners pushed into rapid de-identification should show witness reification more than dissociation. Non-attachment-trained practitioners attempting devotional surrender should show emotional flattening more than spiritual inflation. Devotional practitioners entering analytic deconstruction should show relational rupture or fear of betrayal more than abstract nihilism.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:89:      "difference": "VCE does not claim capacities are directionally pre-shaped toward specific dissolutions or that mismatch predicts specific failures such as witness reification versus emotional flatness.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:55:- Michel Foucault, Technologies of the Self, https://foucault.info/documents/foucault.technologiesOfSelf.en/: overlap: Moderate. Foucault frames self-transforming practices as historically situated techniques involving bodies, souls, thoughts, conduct, truth, and help from others.; difference: Foucault does not give a native authorization-boundary test for contemplative maturity.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for practice as social and ethical technology.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:17:- Advaita, Yoga, Tibetan sleep-yoga, and some objectless-sleep reports claim awareness within the apparent gap.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:18:- Early Buddhist cessation and not-self sources resist turning gap reports into a witness claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:28:Structural observation: Brihadaranyaka 4.3.23 asserts that the seer does not cease in deep sleep, with non-seeing explained by absence of a second object. SN 22.59 applies not-self to consciousness, AN 9.34 names peace through the absence of felt experience, and MN 44 says no thought of I am attaining or emerging occurs in cessation. The candidate correctly identifies two incompatible evidential postures, but the structural split is already central to the classical Indian debate and recent dreamless-sleep research.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before public use, read Thompson on Advaita and Nyaya, Windt, Nielsen, and Thompson on dreamless sleep taxonomy, Alcaraz-Sanchez on objectless sleep, Tibetan clear-light sleep manuals, Yoga Sutra 1.10 commentaries, Mandukya sources, and sleep-state misperception literature. Check Sanskrit and Pali terms before treating English phrases as evidence.
