reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:40:- Nothingness Is All There Is objectless awareness during sleep minimal self agency location
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:41:- Tibetan clear light sleep lucid dreamless sleep witnessing sleep meta-awareness
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:47:- Evan Thompson, Dreamless Sleep, the Embodied Mind, and Consciousness, Open MIND 2015, https://open-mind.net/epubs/dreamless-sleep-the-embodied-mind-and-consciousness-the-relevance-of-a-classical-indian-debate-to-cognitive-science/OEBPS/pt03.html: overlap: Very close. Thompson directly compares memory versus inference, Advaita and Nyaya, retrospective reports, and the possibility of dreamless sleep as objectless awareness.; difference: The candidate turns the debate into a practical routing rule for Lumenary report-grammar work.; novelty impact: Major reduction. The core structure is known; the useful part is operational framing.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:48:- Windt, Nielsen, and Thompson, Does Consciousness Disappear in Dreamless Sleep?, Trends in Cognitive Sciences 2016, https://evanthompson.me/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/does-consciousness-disappear-in-dreamless-sleep_-1.pdf: overlap: Very close. The paper argues dreamless sleep is not uniformly unconscious and asks whether witnessing or contentless sleep reports form a robust subgroup.; difference: It builds a sleep-science taxonomy, not a cross-tradition originality-audit gate.; novelty impact: Strong reduction for the opacity versus awareness split.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:49:- Alcaraz-Sanchez, Awareness in the Void, Phenomenology and the Cognitive Sciences 2023, https://eprints.gla.ac.uk/238595/; Alcaraz-Sanchez et al., Nothingness Is All There Is, Frontiers in Psychology 2022, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2022.901031/full: overlap: Very close empirical-adjacent neighbor. These sources study reports of objectless awareness during sleep and show that supposed awareness of nothing may include minimal self, agency, location, emotion, and non-modal sensation.; difference: They do not formulate a Lumenary opacity versus claimed-transparency rule.; novelty impact: Major reduction and strong anomaly pressure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:50:- Prior Lumenary records: The Gap Report Has a Grammar and The Inferential Gap, observations and originality audits in this repo.: overlap: Decisive internal overlap. Those records already named clear-light sleep and objectless-awareness reports as the anomaly to post-gap report grammar.; difference: This candidate promotes the anomaly into an upstream codebook variable.; novelty impact: Major internal reduction. Treat as an extension, not a standalone discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:51:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 4.3.23 and Yoga Sutra 1.10 as discussed by Thompson, https://vivekavani.com/bru4c3v23/ and https://open-mind.net/epubs/dreamless-sleep-the-embodied-mind-and-consciousness-the-relevance-of-a-classical-indian-debate-to-cognitive-science/OEBPS/pt03.html: overlap: The witness or objectless-consciousness side is primary textual prior art, not new inference.; difference: The candidate refuses to endorse the witness claim and uses it as a classification problem.; novelty impact: Moderate to strong reduction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:52:- Early Buddhist cessation and not-self sources: SN 22.59, AN 9.34, MN 44, dhammatalks.org links above.: overlap: They supply the opposing opacity or non-appropriation rule and make the candidate's contrast old at the primary-text level.; difference: They do not build a comparative codebook for modern discontinuity anxiety.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction, plus anomaly pressure against any hidden-witness reading.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:68:- If: Training background should shape report class before clause-level grammar is analyzed. Then: Witnessing-sleep or clear-light practitioners produce more in-gap presence claims under neutral interviews, while cessation or not-self practitioners produce more edge, transition, and non-appropriation reports. Weakens if: Both groups produce the same report classes, or differences disappear when interviewer prompts and doctrinal vocabulary are controlled. Test surface: Blind-coded micro-phenomenological interviews with Advaita, Tibetan sleep-yoga, Theravada, and untrained participants.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:77:- Theravada teachers familiar with cessation and not-self practice
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:84:- Is opacity versus claimed transparency more than the familiar memory, inference, witness, and cessation debate?
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:110:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.58 to 0.39. The exact structural split is already present in classical Indian debate, contemporary dreamless-sleep taxonomy, objectless-sleep micro-phenomenology, and prior Lumenary gap-report audits. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: discontinuity anxiety and death anxiety after ordinary blank gaps. It is not for trauma amnesia, dissociation, panic disorder, substance blackout, frequent unexplained loss of consciousness, or people who will use the gap to intensify metaphysical rumination.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-not-every-blank-is-an-absence-430e42351b012619.md:114:- Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with The Gap Report Has a Grammar and The Inferential Gap.
