reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:47:- Prior Lumenary audit, Silence Needs Correction, reviews/originality/2026-05-30-silence-needs-correction-06ae06e9a81492e8.json: overlap: Near exact internal prior art. It already says silence after self-questioning becomes usable only when the later report can be corrected by teacher, text, vow, community, clinician, or conduct.; difference: The current idea shifts from correction-holder language to return-discipline language and adds achievement-contingent self-worth as a clearer cohort.; novelty impact: Decisive reduction. Treat as renamed internal work.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:48:- Prior Lumenary records: Keep What Can Correct You, The Test Is How You Return, A Practice Cannot Name Itself, and Every Insight Has An Appeal Court: overlap: Very close. These records already argue that insights and practices must be tested by return, correction, conduct, and non-ownership.; difference: No Silence Proves Itself compresses the cluster into a post-gap slogan and practice prompt.; novelty impact: Major internal reduction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:52:- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, and Progress or Pathology, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full: overlap: Close on appraisal, interpretation, social context, teacher and clinician support, and differential response to meditation-related challenges.; difference: The candidate turns safety and appraisal concerns into a simple post-blank identity-verdict delay.; novelty impact: Moderate to strong reduction, with useful safety support.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:61:Candidate: Direct recognition, clear-light sleep, or stable solitary realization cases where mature practitioners report immediate knowing with ethical integration and no explicit return-discipline gate, plus the opposite anomaly of abusive or compulsive correction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:63:Why it strains the model: If some mature sources and practitioners treat silence or recognition as self-evident in a bounded way, the claim that no silence proves itself is too broad. If correction commonly produces shame, dependence, or coercion, return discipline cannot be presented as a universal first layer.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:69:- If: Return discipline is an independently codable variable, not just a restatement of tradition identity. Then: Blind coders can identify instruction-before, correction-after, conduct-test, relationship-duty, or no-return-discipline from one source layer and predict held-out warnings or repairs better than tradition label alone. Weakens if: Coders need outcome passages to identify return discipline, or tradition label and teacher style predict warnings equally well. Test surface: Split-source coding across Upanishadic, Theravada, Zen, Tibetan, Christian, Sufi, and modern meditation-safety sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:71:- If: Even direct-recognition traditions preserve return constraints. Then: Advaita, Dzogchen, Zen, and apophatic sources that speak strongly about immediate recognition still retain some constraint through teacher, text, lineage, vow, conduct, compassion, or ordinary functioning. Weakens if: Mature sources explicitly authorize private silence as sufficient warrant with no correction, conduct, lineage, or aftercare, and practitioners show stable integration without those constraints. Test surface: Close reading plus practitioner interviews asking for concrete misrecognition, warning, and repair cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:72:- If: Support routing matters more than the first label applied to a difficult blank state. Then: Meditation-related challenge cases improve when interpretation is paired with fitting teacher, community, clinical, or conduct support, rather than relying on spiritual or clinical labeling alone. Weakens if: Clinical-risk variables explain outcomes completely, or return-discipline naming adds no value beyond standard triage. Test surface: Retrospective VCE-style case coding and a prospective support-routing pilot.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:78:- Buddhist meditation teachers in Theravada, Zen, and Tibetan settings
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:79:- Advaita and Dzogchen teachers who teach direct recognition
