reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:93:Answers that support contribution: Practitioners can use return-discipline language to identify overinterpretation earlier, route high-striving practitioners away from worth verdicts, and specify when teacher, text, clinician, conduct, rest, or no-practice is the right holder.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:101:Prediction: Teams or clinicians that require a named return check before acting on a private insight will show fewer overclaimed conclusions, fewer avoidant delays, and fewer identity-protective interpretations than groups relying on intuitive certainty alone.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.42 to 0.18. The teaching is clear and potentially useful, but it is a renamed synthesis of prior Lumenary correction and return records plus close external near-neighbors in Ignatian discernment, James, Alston, Buddhist not-self inspection, and VCE safety literature. Human-condition fit is strong but narrow: stable self-directed practitioners with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, loneliness, or isolated overinterpretation after quiet states. It is not for trauma amnesia, dissociation, panic disorder, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, unexplained loss of consciousness, medical or legal reconstruction, abusive authority contexts, or people already under competent guidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:115:- Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge or cross-index with Silence Needs Correction, Keep What Can Correct You, The Test Is How You Return, and A Practice Cannot Name Itself.
